The paper deals with identifying human actions in videos, which is a problem related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using Convolution Neural Network (CNN) to learn the representation from dense trajectories, which is a technique related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves extracting trajectories and computing trajectory descriptors, which are techniques related to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
